The IAM role sap-hana-backup-role trust policy doesn't allow AWS Backup to assume it.

Go to AWS Console → IAM → Roles → sap-hana-backup-role → Trust relationships → Edit trust policy and make sure it looks like this:

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "Service": [
          "ec2.amazonaws.com",
          "backup.amazonaws.com",
          "ssm.amazonaws.com"
        ]
      },
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole"
    }
  ]
}
The key part is "backup.amazonaws.com" must be in the Principal → Service list. If it only has "ec2.amazonaws.com", add the other two.

